Subject: Broken dvipdfm wrapper script

The "dvipdfm" wrapper script in /usr/local/bin/dvipdfm is broken in
two ways. First, it tries to export a variable using a dollar sign,
which fails instead to export the value of the variable, and second,
the path it supplies isn't sufficient for dvipdfm to find all of its
files.

The attached patch fixes it.

--- /usr/local/bin/dvipdfm	Sat Feb 22 17:07:52 2003
+++ /g6/users/smcc/bin/dvipdfm	Mon Mar  3 13:12:19 2003
@@ -1,8 +1,9 @@
 #!/bin/bash
 
 DVIPDFMHOME=/usr/local/pkg/dvipdfm/dvipdfm-0.13.2c
-DVIPDFMINPUTS=$DVIPDFMHOME/share/texmf/dvipdfm/:
-export $DVIPDFMINPUTS
+top=$DVIPDFMHOME/share/texmf/dvipdfm
+DVIPDFMINPUTS=$top/:$top/base:$top/config
+export DVIPDFMINPUTS
 
 $DVIPDFMHOME/bin/dvipdfm $@
 

===========================================================================
